Rule: Higher education levels (Masters, Bachelors, Prof-school, Some-college) are associated with earning more than $50k a year.
Occupations in White-Collar or Professional categories are more likely to result in an income greater than $50k compared to Blue-Collar jobs.
The type of occupation within a workclass (particularly in self-employed or private) is crucial, with a preference towards White-Collar or Professional roles.
Gender does not solely determine income level, but the presence of both male and female individuals in positive outcomes suggests it is not a limiting factor.
The number of hours worked per week (e.g., 50 hours) does not significantly impact the income prediction by itself.
